00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:09,320
(Her Private Life)

2
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:30,080
(Her Private Life)

3
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:34,680
How old are you?

4
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:36,120
Seven.

5
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:39,120
I'm seven, too, and he's also seven.

6
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:42,560
I'm Sung Duk-mi,

7
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:44,640
and he's Nam Eun-ki.

8
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,520
What's your name?

9
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:49,160
I'm??

10
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:50,720
Heo Yun-je.

11
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:52,120
Are you waiting for your mom?

12
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:54,960
Do you want to play with us?

13
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:19,000
(Episode 15: You are my home)

14
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,120
(You're where I'm meant to be)

15
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,080
Did you sleep well?

16
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,240
Did you sleep well?

17
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,520
Are you still sleeping?

18
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:04,040
It's too early to get up.

19
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,440
But it's your birthday.

20
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,240
Happy Birthday.

21
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,680
Thank you.

22
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,760
You're not even opening your eyes.

23
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,160
Don't you want to see me?

24
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:30,360
Wow, you're the first thing I see as soon as I open my eyes.

25
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,440
What a fantastic birthday.

26
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,160
We should get up now.

27
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:44,840
It's my birthday. I don't have to get up.

28
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,000
Fine, sleep some more.

29
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,480
Should we just stay like this and not go to work?

30
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,960
How about becoming unemployed together?

31
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,000
We could resign.

32
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,120
- I'll get up. - I was being serious.

33
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:04,160
Let's do this all day and not go to work.

34
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,080
- No? - No.

35
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,160
Why not?

36
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,720
Because it's such a waste.

37
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,080
I want to treasure this moment.

38
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:19,960
Duk-mi.

39
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:24,320
You're really damn??

40
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,400
Beautiful, even in the morning, right?

41
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:32,880
I was going to say gross??

42
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,080
Gross?

43
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,560
Don't be scared, now.

44
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,040
I'll still be able to go to work today, right?

45
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,560
- Here we go. - Alright.

46
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,800
Why are you quivering?

47
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,800
No, I'm not.

48
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,880
You don't trust me?

49
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:05,120
What's all this?

50
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,000
It's your birthday, so I need to make you seaweed soup.

51
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,440
- You're going to make it for me? - Yes.

52
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,920
But what are these hot peppers and ginseng?

53
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,240
Hot pepper's something you think tastes good,

54
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:19,080
and the ginseng's something that's good for you.

55
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:20,160
Oh??

56
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:23,640
But I don't think these guys should make it into our soup??

57
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,280
Really?

58
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,440
Then I'll make you kimbap with these later.

59
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:28,440
Alright!

60
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,440
Yum, ginseng kimbap.

61
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,680
This much should be fine, right?

62
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:45,160
Director, this thing has 60 servings,

63
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,520
so with that, we'll have plenty for 20 people.

64
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,760
Then??

65
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:52,760
About this much?

66
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,720
I'll cook it up real nice, just wait a little while.

67
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:58,320
Yes, I trust that you will.

68
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,600
This one?

69
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,000
Yes, it's nice.

70
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,040
Oh! You should get changed, too.

71
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,480
I was planning to just go in this.

72
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,320
I'm starting to think we're sharing too much of

73
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,000
our private lives with the museum staff.

74
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,120
Are you embarrassed, shy boy?

75
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,320
Then wear something of mine. I'll pick it out for you.

76
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,440
Oh, no.

77
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:22,640
I can drop by my house and change into my own clothes.

78
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,120
But I think this would look nice on you.

79
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,600
What is it?

80
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:32,760
What do you want?

81
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,080
I'll do it for you.

82
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,760
Have you ever done it before?

83
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,320
I'm Ryan Gold.

84
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,120
Beautiful.

85
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,760
Let me put some on you, too.

86
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,200
I think you need a little more.

87
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,600
Do I have to go to work looking like this?

88
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,920
You look nice.

89
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,360
You look like you've got some life in you now.

90
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:43,760
Can I be queen for the day, since it's my birthday?

91
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,160
I look like a celebrity, don't I?

92
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,720
Oppa, have some of this as you go.

93
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,200
Thanks, Sun-joo.

94
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,800
Are you working? Is this a proposal for a new show?

95
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,160
No.

96
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:43,920
I said I'd live to make you smile from now on, didn't I?

97
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:46,040
So I was thinking about what I could do with you,

98
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,000
and made a proposal.

99
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,560
You even wrote a proposal?

100
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,680
Have a look.

101
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,960
The title is "How About Camping?"

102
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,880
- Camping? - Yes.

103
00:07:55,880 --> 00:08:00,040
Every weekend, you, Gun-woo and I will go camping.

104
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,760
We'll cook outdoors,

105
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:04,200
watch the stars at night and just chill.

106
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,280
But do we have a tent?

107
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,240
We should get one.

108
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:10,120
And there are so many other things you need for camping.

109
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,160
You need pots, burners, and??That's right, lantern.

110
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,720
Oppa??

111
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,920
You know that I'm particular about where I sleep.

112
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,000
Oh, I forgot. Then, uh??

113
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,560
Should we just buy an RV?

114
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,880
Uh-uh.

115
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:29,120
- Anything else? - Of course I have others.

116
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,680
The title of the second proposal is

117
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,160
"Fishing Over Flowers."

118
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,000
- Fishing? - Yes.

119
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,080
I hear night fishing is great.

120
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,000
But rather than fishing,

121
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,920
it's about spending time together and talking to each other.

122
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:44,120
And at night, we'll sleep in tents??

123
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,080
Ugh, again with the tents?

124
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:47,440
If sleeping in tents is not your thing,

125
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,840
then I guess an RV is the way to go?

126
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,000
- Oppa. - Yeah?

127
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:56,040
How about instead of doing things to please me

128
00:08:56,040 --> 00:09:00,000
you just try not to do things I don't like?

129
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,360
- Not do things you don't like? - Yes.

130
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:05,160
Okay, I totally got it.

131
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,960
Then??In order to find out what you don't like,

132
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,400
we need to spend some time chatting, so the fishing??

133
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,520
Don't, I said don't! Just stop it already.

134
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,680
Alright, alright.

135
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,000
I'm going to work!

136
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:18,520
Let's talk a lot tonight.

137
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,640
About what you don't like??

138
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,640
while fishing.

139
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,080
Just go! Go! Go!

140
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,680
What's wrong with him?

141
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,920
If laughing in disbelief is still considered laughing,

142
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,480
then your husband has succeeded.

143
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:36,160
Isn't my Seung-min just too cute?

144
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:39,080
This is the final layout of our exhibition space.

145
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,160
Did you run a simulation on the expected route?

146
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:44,160
Yes, we think Mr. Cha Si-an's hall will be the busiest,

147
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:47,000
so we assigned him the biggest space.

148
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,360
Oh, the partitions will be up starting next week.

149
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:52,040
Once they're up, we'll start painting the walls.

150
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:54,080
How about you go for a stronger color

151
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,160
for the main entrance wall as an accent?

152
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,680
Oh. Sure.

153
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,280
How's the recruiting going?

154
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:04,440
We've already recruited our docents and helpers,

155
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,920
and training will begin next week.

156
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:10,040
Alright, so we're almost set.

157
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:13,480
Ah! You need to prepare a speech for the opening day.

158
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,560
Got it.

159
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,280
- Duk-mi! - Yes?

160
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:25,440
I know we're both busy, but this is our first birthday together.

161
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,160
You'll make time this evening, right?

162
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,080
I'll see what I can do.

163
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,120
What's our goal for today?

164
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,000
To get off work on time.

165
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:49,120
Your mom said to wait at the playground?

166
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:53,040
Yes, she said she'd come soon.

167
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:57,160
What's your name?

168
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:59,280
Yun-je.

169
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,680
Heo Yun-je.

170
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:03,720
Yun-je, you must be hungry.

171
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,840
Do you want to come to our house for dinner?

172
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,400
What is it?

173
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,760
Duk-mi and Eun-ki will be there, too.

174
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:16,720
I have to wait for my mom at the playground.

175
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,480
Um??

176
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:22,040
Then I'll wait here instead,

177
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:24,640
and let you know once your mother is here.

178
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:25,760
How does that sound?

179
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:30,040
Alright, off you go to eat!

180
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:33,000
- And wash your hands! - Okay!

181
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,600
Gosh, what do you keep looking at this for?

182
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:50,880
Why do you think Eun-ki asked about his name?

183
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,160
He said he just did.

184
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:57,120
Eun-ki??

185
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,040
That boy has never once mentioned that day,

186
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:01,800
not even by accident.

187
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,320
You've no idea how grateful and guilty I've felt about that.

188
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:14,280
I think there's something he can't tell me.

189
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:20,120
If it's something he can't tell you, he won't say it.

190
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:23,160
And if it's something he must, he'll say it.

191
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,320
Just wait.

192
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,000
Duk-mi, do you want to go in first?

193
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,000
Why? Let's go in together.

194
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,120
I think we're a little late for our reservation.

195
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,440
Oh. Sure.

196
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,160
Welcome. Do you have a reservation?

197
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:57,120
Yes, under Ryan Gold.

198
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:04,360
Happy birthday to you!

199
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:08,040
Happy birthday to you!

200
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,240
Happy birthday, Duk-mi.

201
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,680
Mr. Cha Si-an??

202
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,960
First, make a wish.

203
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:28,640
I have no more wishes now.

204
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:31,120
Oh!

205
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,000
I know my brother's pretty awesome,

206
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,280
but he's going to be a little late after planning this all.

207
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:36,800
Don't hold it against him today.

208
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,280
Director Gold's going to be late?

209
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:41,160
Yes, he said he was running late

210
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,400
and asked me to keep you company in the meantime.

211
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,600
That's why I ran here, at the speed of light.

212
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,160
It's nice that you're seeing Director Gold and Ms. Sung Duk-mi,

213
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:53,640
but I hope you're not interrupting them.

214
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,320
Mom, what's with "Director Gold"?

215
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:58,720
It's Yun-je. Heo Yun-je.

216
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,160
And what if I do interrupt them?

217
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:03,120
A little is fine.

218
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,040
Alright.

219
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,120
Here's your mission.

220
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:13,120
Go to the next room alone, most definitely alone,

221
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,800
and sing happy birthday to Ms. Sung Duk-mi.

222
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,320
I'm running a little late.

223
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,120
Who is it?

224
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,960
It's brother.

225
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,040
Mom, one minute.

226
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,720
Really?

227
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:30,480
Yes! I didn't even know today was your birthday.

228
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,760
If I'd known, I would've prepared a gift.

229
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:36,840
My Si-an??You're the gift!

230
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,160
One moment.

231
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,760
Do you like my present?

232
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,680
- Is it brother? - Yes.

233
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:55,800
Director, I'm the happiest fangirl in the world right now.

234
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:57,040
Thank you so much!

235
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:04,120
But just 20 minutes, alright?

236
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:07,760
And don't get more excited than when you're with me.

237
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:14,520
It's Ms. Sung Duk-mi's birthday so you should spend it together

238
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:15,800
just the two of you, instead of calling us.

239
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,040
It's alright.

240
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:19,640
I'm sure Duk-mi will like this, too.

241
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:23,200
Let's wait for 20 minutes and go over together.

242
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,240
20 minutes?

243
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,680
Because it's nice,

244
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:32,680
being here just the two of us.

245
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,640
Thank you.

246
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:38,240
For calling me mom.

247
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:44,360
To be honest with you, I still find it a little awkward.

248
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:48,360
But I promise I'll get used to it with time.

249
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:51,040
Though it may be awkward for you, too,

250
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,160
please call me by my name.

251
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,640
Yun-je.

252
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,080
Yes, Mother.

253
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:09,520
It's Ms. Sung Duk-mi's birthday today but I'm getting a gift.

254
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:14,000
September 12th.

255
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:20,160
Your birthday, Yun-je, is September 12th.

256
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,120
September 12th??

257
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,440
Let's spend it together this year, no matter what.

258
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:35,680
By the way, I brought some photos along.

259
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,240
There aren't many, but??

260
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:48,960
This is how I remembered you all these years.

261
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:52,880
I always wondered how much you'd grown up when you were 10,

262
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:56,120
and what you looked like when you were twenty.

263
00:16:56,120 --> 00:17:00,560
You have no idea how much I missed you.

264
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:14,000
I'll show you.

265
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:18,280
What I looked like when I was ten, and when I was twenty.

266
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,160
I've got quite a lot of pictures.

267
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,160
I see.

268
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,240
Do you see that?

269
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:44,960
Ah, Director!

270
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,040
Hello.

