Don't cry.

568
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:01,760
Don't cry.

569
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:22,360
I'm sorry, Mom, for not remembering.

570
00:46:22,360 --> 00:46:24,480
For making things harder on you.

571
00:46:24,480 --> 00:46:29,760
Back then, it was thanks to you that I was able to live on.

572
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:38,480
It's thanks to you forgetting everything and

573
00:46:38,480 --> 00:46:41,600
growing up bright and cheerful

574
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:45,120
that I was able to make it no matter how tough it was.

575
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:49,560
I'm still sorry.

576
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:54,640
For being the only one going on as if nothing happened

577
00:46:54,640 --> 00:46:57,600
when everyone else had to live with painful memories.

578
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:59,520
I'm sorry for being such a coward.

579
00:47:03,120 --> 00:47:05,000
They said that when they found you

580
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:10,920
you were holding onto Duk-su's hand and wouldn't let go.

581
00:47:13,120 --> 00:47:15,200
So I'm sure Duk-su wasn't scared

582
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:17,840
on his journey to the other world.

583
00:47:18,560 --> 00:47:20,920
I know

584
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:23,920
just how much you loved and cared for Duk-su.

585
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:27,120
So it's alright.

586
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:29,040
It's all alright, Duk-mi.

587
00:47:30,560 --> 00:47:33,920
I remember everything now.

588
00:47:35,040 --> 00:47:37,800
Both Director Gold and Duk-su.

589
00:47:39,200 --> 00:47:41,200
Mom, let's??

590
00:47:41,200 --> 00:47:44,960
Let's not swallow what we want to say.

591
00:47:46,040 --> 00:47:47,960
Let's share it,

592
00:47:48,800 --> 00:47:51,080
and let's remember Duk-su.

593
00:47:54,120 --> 00:47:55,680
Thank you, my dear daughter.

594
00:47:58,120 --> 00:47:59,200
Thank you.

595
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:11,240
Oh, that's right.

596
00:48:11,240 --> 00:48:12,480
Duk-mi.

597
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:15,320
Eun-ki??

598
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:20,280
That young thing??

599
00:48:20,280 --> 00:48:24,280
What happened to Duk-su and your illness in the aftermath??

600
00:48:24,280 --> 00:48:26,760
Seeing as that he watched it all from the sidelines

601
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:29,080
and endured it all without complaint,

602
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:33,440
I'm sure he had a tough time, too, though he's never said anything.

603
00:48:45,160 --> 00:48:46,280
Eun-ki.

604
00:48:48,680 --> 00:48:54,480
Thank you for comforting Mom and Dad all this time.

605
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:03,000
When I think about it,

606
00:49:04,720 --> 00:49:09,360
it was you who always stayed by my side and protected me,

607
00:49:09,360 --> 00:49:12,120
and I took it for granted.

608
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:14,680
Because??

609
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:18,960
You're my Eun-ki bastard.

610
00:49:18,960 --> 00:49:22,000
That was just me fanboying, FYI.

611
00:49:26,240 --> 00:49:28,000
- Duk-mi. - Hm?

612
00:49:28,880 --> 00:49:30,520
Are you alright?

613
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:33,000
No, I'm not alright.

614
00:49:36,040 --> 00:49:39,000
How did you take all this? You were so little, too.

615
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:44,120
We're family, that's how.

616
00:49:55,120 --> 00:49:58,000
I'm really grateful to that

617
00:49:58,000 --> 00:49:59,440
seven-year-old Eun-ki right now.

618
00:50:00,280 --> 00:50:05,040
And also to the 33-year-old Eun-ki,

619
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:07,400
who's in front of me, right now.

620
00:50:07,400 --> 00:50:08,800
I'm sorry, too.

621
00:50:10,400 --> 00:50:12,080
Hey, Duk-mi.

622
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:14,080
I guess I only told you that you're pretty when you smile,

623
00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:16,080
but never this:

624
00:50:17,120 --> 00:50:19,480
You're really ugly when you cry.

625
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:22,480
Liar.

626
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,680
I'm not lying.

627
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:31,480
You're going to tell him, right?

628
00:50:31,480 --> 00:50:32,640
Director Gold, I mean.

629
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:36,920
You can do it, Duk-mi!

630
00:50:47,160 --> 00:50:49,160
- Hello, Director. - Hello!

631
00:50:52,160 --> 00:50:55,480
Right, Curator Sung is a little late today.

632
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:57,040
Please give them some time.

633
00:50:57,040 --> 00:50:59,160
Time for Mom to tell Duk-mi everything,

634
00:50:59,160 --> 00:51:02,040
and time for Duk-mi to take it all in.

635
00:51:02,040 --> 00:51:04,120
Curator Sung will be taking the day??

636
00:51:04,120 --> 00:51:05,320
Good morning.

637
00:51:09,440 --> 00:51:11,080
I'm here, Director.

638
00:51:11,760 --> 00:51:13,200
Duk-mi.

639
00:51:13,200 --> 00:51:15,000
I have something to tell you.

640
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:31,320
- Duk-mi. - Director.

641
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:40,440
I heard from Eun-ki that your memory returned.

642
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:49,040
I was so distressed I didn't know what to do.

643
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:50,640
I just wanted to go into hiding??

644
00:51:50,640 --> 00:51:51,880
Don't do that.

645
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:55,160
If you do that, I'll really struggle.

646
00:51:58,040 --> 00:52:00,080
I thought you would,

647
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:03,880
so I decided to just face you with a smile.

648
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:08,440
I thought that struggling together

649
00:52:08,440 --> 00:52:10,440
might be better than struggling alone.

650
00:52:12,840 --> 00:52:14,000
Thank you.

651
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:16,280
Mom's??

652
00:52:18,280 --> 00:52:21,000
My mom's here.

653
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:24,560
She wanted to apologize to you in person.

654
00:52:27,640 --> 00:52:30,120
My mom??My mom??

655
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:32,120
It's alright, Duk-mi.

656
00:52:32,120 --> 00:52:33,080
It's really alright.

657
00:52:50,360 --> 00:52:51,640
I'll be back.

658
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:54,520
Wait here.

659
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:30,000
I heard from Duk-mi

660
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:34,400
that your mother couldn't come because she was in an accident.

661
00:53:35,320 --> 00:53:40,960
I should have kept you with us a little longer.

662
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:43,160
Then all this time, you wouldn't have had to??

663
00:53:51,080 --> 00:53:52,440
I'm sorry.

664
00:53:56,200 --> 00:53:57,360
Mother.

665
00:53:59,000 --> 00:54:04,040
I heard that's how you address your girlfriend's parents

666
00:54:04,040 --> 00:54:06,680
in Korea. "Mother" and "Father".

667
00:54:06,680 --> 00:54:10,040
I've come to have many mothers ever since coming to Korea.

668
00:54:11,080 --> 00:54:14,000
I found my birth mother,

669
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:16,480
and now I can call you "mother," as well.

670
00:54:17,960 --> 00:54:23,560
I don't deserve to be called that by you.

671
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:27,000
I know it's too late to seek your forgiveness, but??

672
00:54:29,040 --> 00:54:30,400
I'm sorry.

673
00:54:31,440 --> 00:54:33,960
If it weren't for you,

674
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:37,040
I really would've been an abandoned child

675
00:54:37,040 --> 00:54:39,160
in an unfamiliar neighborhood.

676
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:42,440
You took me, a complete stranger, in,

677
00:54:42,440 --> 00:54:44,560
fed me,

678
00:54:44,560 --> 00:54:46,520
and looked after me.

679
00:54:51,960 --> 00:54:53,080
Thank you.

680
00:55:02,480 --> 00:55:05,120
I'm too late in saying this,

681
00:55:05,120 --> 00:55:07,840
but thank you so much for

682
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:09,760
looking after me,

683
00:55:12,120 --> 00:55:14,120
and giving me love, Mother.

684
00:55:36,560 --> 00:55:42,080
I decided to go see Duk-su's resting place with Mom.

685
00:55:43,560 --> 00:55:46,960
Apparently, they went to see him every year without me.

686
00:55:49,880 --> 00:55:51,120
And??

687
00:55:52,400 --> 00:55:57,040
I will always be sorry about

688
00:55:57,040 --> 00:55:59,200
Mom putting you in an orphanage.

689
00:56:08,240 --> 00:56:09,440
Duk-mi.

690
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:13,040
Those memories??

691
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:19,160
They may have hurt seven-year-old Yun-je,

692
00:56:19,840 --> 00:56:22,440
but they mean nothing to present me.

693
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:24,600
So please??

694
00:56:26,800 --> 00:56:30,280
Stop feeling so sorry.

695
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:31,280
Alright?

696
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:36,080
Good memories,

697
00:56:38,000 --> 00:56:39,320
good times??

698
00:56:42,800 --> 00:56:45,120
Give me lots of those now.

699
00:56:45,120 --> 00:56:46,560
Lots and lots.

700
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:52,400
I??

701
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:55,640
I'll love you more.

702
00:56:57,040 --> 00:56:59,520
So that you can be happy.

703
00:57:01,880 --> 00:57:04,080
I'm already receiving  that kind of love.

704
00:57:11,600 --> 00:57:13,440
And take me with you

705
00:57:14,760 --> 00:57:16,120
when you go see Duk-su.

706
00:57:31,360 --> 00:57:34,360
Yes, that's right. That's right!

707
00:57:39,480 --> 00:57:40,920
Whoa, careful!

708
00:57:48,640 --> 00:57:49,600
Go!

709
00:57:51,120 --> 00:57:52,120
Aren't you going?

710
00:57:54,240 --> 00:57:56,120
Mister, when will you be done?

711
00:57:56,120 --> 00:57:57,080
Why are you asking me this?

712
00:57:57,080 --> 00:57:59,160
If you're done, drive me home.

713
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:01,000
You'll be going that way, anyhow.

714
00:58:03,720 --> 00:58:05,520
I'm curious about something.

715
00:58:05,520 --> 00:58:07,040
Do I look like a pushover to you?

716
00:58:07,960 --> 00:58:09,240
A little?

717
00:58:09,240 --> 00:58:11,440
I'm not done with my classes, so take the bus home!

718
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:17,600
By the way, mister??

719
00:58:18,400 --> 00:58:20,040
I told you not to call me "mister".

720
00:58:20,040 --> 00:58:21,840
This place??

721
00:58:21,840 --> 00:58:24,480
Do you give discounts to acquaintances?

722
00:58:26,840 --> 00:58:28,160
Of course, Ms. Potential Customer.

723
00:58:29,560 --> 00:58:31,760
I can give you a 20% discount,

724
00:58:31,760 --> 00:58:34,120
and a further 10% off if you bring a friend.

725
00:58:34,120 --> 00:58:35,800
So, will you be signing up?

726
00:58:36,160 --> 00:58:37,160
No!

727
00:58:39,800 --> 00:58:40,800
Hey, come here.

728
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:42,600
Hey! Hey!

729
00:58:43,280 --> 00:58:44,960
(Community Center)

730
00:58:47,080 --> 00:58:49,160
I like everything you make, Mom!

731
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:57,760
Since when was she her mother? And why?

732
00:58:57,760 --> 00:58:59,000
Oh my God!

733
00:59:00,880 --> 00:59:03,040
Ma'am, the family register.

734
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:05,440
(Family register: Eom So-hye/Kim Hyo-jin)

735
00:59:07,320 --> 00:59:10,160
Okay, so she's still on the family register.

736
00:59:10,160 --> 00:59:12,400
- Let's go! - Where to?

737
00:59:12,400 --> 00:59:14,680
To get my daughter, where else?

738
00:59:14,680 --> 00:59:16,520
- Quickly, quickly! - Yes, ma'am.

739
00:59:25,200 --> 00:59:27,000
What did the Director say?

740
00:59:29,360 --> 00:59:32,960
He said he's fine, and comforted me instead.

741
00:59:34,480 --> 00:59:37,120
I felt so bad and so grateful at the same time??

742
00:59:44,880 --> 00:59:45,920
Mother?

743
00:59:47,640 --> 00:59:49,120
How did you??

744
00:59:51,320 --> 00:59:53,240
Did you follow me?

745
00:59:53,240 --> 00:59:55,040
Who was the one who told me to get out?

746
00:59:55,040 --> 00:59:56,120
Why are you here?

747
00:59:57,120 --> 00:59:58,160
Hyo-jin?

748
00:59:58,160 --> 01:00:01,240
Should we have a little chat at home?

749
01:00:01,240 --> 01:00:02,240
Let's go.

750
01:00:04,760 --> 01:00:07,080
This is my home now!

751
01:00:07,080 --> 01:00:08,920
Oh my God??

752
01:00:08,920 --> 01:00:10,800
What are your thoughts?

753
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:12,040
Well, grab her!

754
01:00:12,040 --> 01:00:13,440
- Let's go. - Let go! I'm not going.

755
01:00:13,440 --> 01:00:15,000
- I said, let's go! - I'm not going!

756
01:00:15,000 --> 01:00:16,120
Hey!

757
01:00:16,120 --> 01:00:17,200
Let go of me!

758
01:00:18,120 --> 01:00:20,440
I'm so glad he was adopted by a good family??

759
01:00:20,440 --> 01:00:22,880
I said I'm not going!

760
01:00:22,880 --> 01:00:24,440
- What's this sound? - What's all the noise?

761
01:00:24,440 --> 01:00:27,240
I said I'm not going! Let go of me! Mom!

762
01:00:27,240 --> 01:00:29,640
- Open the door. - I'm not going!

763
01:00:29,640 --> 01:00:31,480
What??What is this?

764
01:00:31,480 --> 01:00:33,320
What do you think you people are doing?

765
01:00:33,320 --> 01:00:35,920
Who are you people, and where are you taking our daughter?

766
01:00:35,920 --> 01:00:38,640
Hyo-jin's my daughter!

767
01:00:38,640 --> 01:00:41,120
She's my daughter, so why are you doing this?

768
01:00:41,120 --> 01:00:43,200
She's my daughter, so move it!

769
01:00:43,200 --> 01:00:45,080
Secretary Kim, tell them to move. Tell them!

770
01:00:45,080 --> 01:00:46,400
- Please excuse me. - Move it!

771
01:00:46,400 --> 01:00:47,680
Hyo-jin's my daughter!

772
01:00:47,680 --> 01:00:50,080
Hey, Hyo-jin! Are you my daughter or not?

773
01:00:50,080 --> 01:00:52,280
She's my daughter, yet??Oh my God! Oh my God!

774
01:00:52,280 --> 01:00:53,800
Secretary Kim, what are your thoughts on this?

775
01:00:53,800 --> 01:00:55,360
Oh my God! Move!

776
01:01:04,920 --> 01:01:08,400
We're sorry, we didn't realize you were her mother.

777
01:01:08,400 --> 01:01:10,080
How could you not,

778
01:01:10,080 --> 01:01:12,000
when we look exactly the same?

779
01:01:18,080 --> 01:01:19,840
Hyo-jin,

780
01:01:19,840 --> 01:01:21,960
pack your bags and go with your mother.

781
01:01:21,960 --> 01:01:23,040
But Mom??

782
01:01:23,920 --> 01:01:25,760
Why do you keep on calling her mom?

783
01:01:27,200 --> 01:01:30,640
She was wrong to make you pack your bags and leave,

784
01:01:30,640 --> 01:01:32,160
but now that she's come for you,

785
01:01:32,160 --> 01:01:34,720
you should give her a chance and go with her.

786
01:01:39,240 --> 01:01:40,840
And Hyo-jin's mother?

787
01:01:40,840 --> 01:01:43,080
I'm Eom So-hye.

788
01:01:43,080 --> 01:01:44,360
Hyo-jin's mother?

789
01:01:45,480 --> 01:01:48,320
I know that some people hate being called

790
01:01:48,320 --> 01:01:50,800
so-and-so's mom, so-and-so's mom.

791
01:01:50,800 --> 01:01:54,080
But perhaps because I'm an old lady? I really like it.

792
01:01:54,080 --> 01:01:57,040
I really like it when people call me Duk-mi's mother.

793
01:01:57,800 --> 01:01:59,760
It feels like the whole world is hailing me for

794
01:01:59,760 --> 01:02:02,440
being a mother to my dear daughter.

795
01:02:04,120 --> 01:02:05,560
But you know??

796
01:02:05,560 --> 01:02:08,080
That moment doesn't last forever.

797
01:02:08,080 --> 01:02:10,600
Right now she's your baby,

798
01:02:10,600 --> 01:02:13,920
but she'll leave the nest one day.

799
01:02:13,920 --> 01:02:16,520
So be good to her while she's still in your nest.

800
01:02:16,520 --> 01:02:18,840
It's like people say: Be good to them while you can.

801
01:02:20,360 --> 01:02:23,360
Isn't that usually what we say to the children?

802
01:02:23,360 --> 01:02:25,960
"Be good to your parents while they're still with you."

803
01:02:25,960 --> 01:02:27,360
It goes both ways.

804
01:02:27,360 --> 01:02:29,800
You have to be good to each other while you're both around.

805
01:02:30,960 --> 01:02:33,160
Once you hurt them and find the distance growing between you,

806
01:02:33,160 --> 01:02:35,280
there's no use regretting it.

807
01:02:37,200 --> 01:02:39,560
Just because she's your child doesn't mean you can do

808
01:02:39,560 --> 01:02:42,320
as you please. Being family doesn't let you do that.

809
01:02:42,320 --> 01:02:43,680
Whether it's between husband and wife,

810
01:02:43,680 --> 01:02:46,560
mother and daughter, or siblings,

811
01:02:46,560 --> 01:02:48,520
we're all human and those are all human relationships.

812
01:02:48,520 --> 01:02:51,280
No relationships should be taken for granted.

813
01:02:52,360 --> 01:02:55,400
So even if you're a little clumsy,

814
01:02:55,400 --> 01:02:58,600
as long as you're making the effort, I say it's alright.

815
01:03:00,000 --> 01:03:01,040
You understand, right?

